{{italic title}} {{Taxobox | color = lightgrey | name = Acidicapsa ligni | image = | image_caption = | regnum = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Acidobacteria]] | classis = [[Acidobacteria]] | ordo = [[Acidobacteriales]] | familia = [[Acidobacteriaceae]] | genus = ''[[Acidicapsa]]'' | species = '''''A. ligni''''' | binomial = ''Acidicapsa ligni'' | binomial_authority = Kulichevskaya et al. 2012<ref name=Acidicapsa-ligni>{{cite journal|last1=Parte|first1=A.C.|title=Acidicapsa|journal=www.bacterio.net|url=http://www.bacterio.net/acidicapsa.html}}</ref> | type_strain = LMG 26244, NCCB 100371, VKM B-2677, WH120<ref>{{cite journal|title=Acidicapsa ligni Taxon Passport - StrainInfo|journal=www.straininfo.net|url=http://www.straininfo.net/taxa/380811}}</ref> | subdivision = | synonyms = }}
'''''Acidicapsa ligni''''' is a [[Gram-negative]], short rods and non-motile bacterium from the genus of [[Acidicapsa]] which has been isolated from decaying wood from a [[broadleaf forest]] in [[Netherlands]].<ref name=Acidicapsa-ligni/><ref>{{cite journal|title=Acidicapsa ligni|journal=www.uniprot.org|url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/542300}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Kulichevskaya|first1=I. S.|last2=Kostina|first2=L. A.|last3=Valaskova|first3=V.|last4=Rijpstra|first4=W. I. C.|last5=Sinninghe Damste|first5=J. S.|last6=de Boer|first6=W.|last7=Dedysh|first7=S. N.|title=Acidicapsa borealis gen. nov., sp. nov. and Acidicapsa ligni sp. nov., subdivision 1 Acidobacteria from Sphagnum peat and decaying wood|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|date=19 August 2011|volume=62|issue=Pt 7|pages=1512–1520|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.034819-0|pmid=21856984}}</ref>
