{{Infobox scientist | honorific_prefix = Dr. | name = Hugo Peter Kortschak | honorific_suffix = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = <!--(filename only, i.e. without "File:" prefix) will add photo if can obtain permission to one.--> | image_size = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- if different from "name" --> | birth_date = {{birth date |1911|09|27}} | birth_place = [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]] | death_date = {{death date and age |1983|08|20 |1911|09|27}} | death_place = [[Honolulu]], [[Hawaii]] | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | other_names = | pronounce = | residence = 3522 Maunaloa Avenue, [[Honolulu]], [[Hawaii]] | citizenship = | nationality = | fields = | workplaces = | patrons = | education = | alma_mater = | thesis_title = <!--(or | thesis1_title = and | thesis2_title = )--> | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = <!--(or | thesis1_year = and | thesis2_year = )--> | doctoral_advisor = <!--(or | doctoral_advisors = )--> | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = Discovering the [[C4 pathway]] in 1957 | influences = | influenced = | awards = | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = Kate Leilani Kortschak | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = * Alice M Kortschak * Nonnie Winifred Kortschak | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }}
'''Hugo Peter Kortschak''' (or Kortschack; 4 September 1911, in [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]] – 20 August 1983)<ref name="geni">{{cite web |url=https://www.geni.com/people/Hugo-P-Kortschak/6000000049656984196 |title=Hugo P. Kortschak |date=11 November 2016 |website=geni.com |access-date=1 January 2017 }}</ref> was an American [[biologist]] who discovered the [[C4 pathway]] in 1957. This pathway is an adaptation found in plants which reduces loss of [[energy]] via the inefficient [[photorespiration|C2 pathway]]. It is found in several plants, such as [[maize]] and [[sugarcane]]. The C4 pathway was rediscovered by [[Marshall Hatch|Hatch]] and Slack (to whom the discovery is sometimes wrongly credited).<ref>Nickell, Louis G. (1993). "A tribute to Hugo P. Kortschak: The man, the scientist and the discoverer of C4 photosynthesis". Photosynthesis Research 35 (2): 201.</ref> He was the son of the Austrian-American violinist [[Hugo Kortschak]], father of Alice M Kortschak and Nonnie Winifred Kortschak.<ref name="geni" />
