'''Reinier Cornelis Bakhuizen van den Brink''' (30 January 1881, [[Pasoeroean]] – 4 April 1945, [[Tjimahi]]) was a [[Dutch people|Dutch]] [[botany|botanist]]. He was the son of Henriëtte Maria Raedt van Oldenbarnevelt (1858–1929) and Charles René Bakhuizen van den Brink (1850–1923), and a grandson of the literary critic, historian and philosopher {{Interlanguage link multi|Reinier Cornelis Bakhuizen van den Brink (born 1810)|nl|3=Reinier Cornelis Bakhuizen van den Brink|lt=Reinier Cornelis Bakhuizen van den Brink}} (1810–1865).<ref name=gen>[https://dziewon.home.xs4all.nl/stamboom/bb029.htm Genealogy of Reinier Cornelis Bakhuizen van den Brink [2]</ref>
In 1917 he married Djahini from Tjimahi, whom he had met in 1910. Their son [[Reinier Cornelis Bakhuizen van den Brink (born 1911)|Reinier Cornelis]] (1911–1987) was also a botanist.<ref name=gen/>

